Package: mcceR
Title:  Monte Carlo sampling of realistic Counterfactual Explanations for tabular data
Version: 0.0.1.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Martin", "Jullum", email = "Martin.Jullum@nr.no", role = c("cre", "aut"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3908-5155")),
    person("Annabelle", "Redelmeier", email = "Annabelle.Redelmeier@nr.no", role = "aut"),
    person("Anders", "Løland", email = "Anders.Loland@nr.no", role = "ctb"), 
    person("Norsk Regnesentral", role =  c("cph", "fnd"))
    )
Description: mcceR generate counterfactual explanations for any tabular data model using the method described in 
  Redelmeier, A., Jullum, M., Aas, K. and Løland, A. (2021) <arXiv:2111.09790>.
  A Python wrapper (mcceRpy) is also available to explain models fitted in Python.
